==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Andromed
<hw>An"dro*med</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr> }</mhw>, <pos>n.</pos>} <fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>A meteor
appearing to radiate from a point in the constellation Andromeda, --
whence the name.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><note>⟦hand⟧ A shower of these meteors takes place every year on
November 27th or 28th. The Andromedes are also called
<altname>Bielids</altname>, as they are connected with Biela's comet and
move in its orbit.</note>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Andron</ent>⟦br⟧
